From: Yang Shi <yang.shi@windriver.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Oct 2012 15:02:54 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] net: Remove IFF_LIVE_ADDR_CHANGE in NTB netdev driver

The IFF_LIVE_ADDR_CHANGE flag added by the upstream commit
bb35f67195fcdbe79faa7a15ce148a67c9ab923d [net: introduce new priv_flag
indicating iface capable of change mac when running] added in 3.6 is used by
NTB but not available in 3.4, so removing its use here.

Signed-off-by: Yang Shi <yang.shi@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/ntb_netdev.c |    2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ntb_netdev.c b/drivers/net/ntb_netdev.c
index bc76c63..a80c1b0 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ntb_netdev.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ntb_netdev.c
@@ -331,8 +331,6 @@ static int __devinit ntb_netdev_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev)
 	BUG_ON(!dev->pdev);
 	ndev->features = NETIF_F_HIGHDMA;
 
-	ndev->priv_flags |= IFF_LIVE_ADDR_CHANGE;
-
 	ndev->hw_features = ndev->features;
 	ndev->watchdog_timeo = msecs_to_jiffies(NTB_TX_TIMEOUT_MS);
 
